eu.slipo.athenarc.triplegeo.tools

Class RdfToShp

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.slipo.athenarc.triplegeo.tools.RdfToShp
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ReverseConverter

    public class RdfToShp
extends java.lang.Object
implements ReverseConverter
    Main entry point of the utility for reconverting triples from a RDF graph into an ESRI Shapefile. LIMITATIONS: The Shapefile format has several limitations: - The GEOMETRY attribute is always declared first, and can only store geometries of a single type; - Geometries must be of one of the following types: Point, MultiPoint, MuiltiLineString, MultiPolygon; - Attribute names are limited in length (max 10 characters); otherwise, they get truncated; - Not all data types can be supported (e.g., Timestamp values must be represented as Strings).
    Version:
    1.8
    Author:
    Kostas Patroumpas
